@@yThe Vault Antechamber@@N~
The first proper room of the Eternal Vault has a formal quality that exceeds the floors below: the @@bsandstone@@N block-work is more precise, the inscriptions denser, and the @@yyellow@@N gold paint in the cartouche borders is the most intact of any on the ascending floors. The antechamber records the vault's creation, its purpose, and the names of all the beings interred within it — a complete roster of the pyramid's secondary pharaoh-lords arranged in order of their binding date. The list is long.
~
