@@yA Sealed Side Chamber@@N~
A side chamber whose entrance is sealed with a @@bsandstone@@N block set in a mortared frame, the mortar cracked and partially fallen out, leaving a narrow gap at the block's lower right corner through which cold air sighs steadily outward. What lies within cannot be seen from the entrance, but the air carries the smell of old preservatives and something else — the faint residue of whatever spiritual presence occupied this space at the sealing.
~
