#10269
@@yThe Hall of Eternal Rest@@N~
Sealed sarcophagi occupy wall recesses the length of this hall on both sides, each one sealed with a mortared stone panel carved with the occupant's name, titles, and a brief protective formula. The sarcophagi are intact, their seals unbroken, their contents — if still present — immovable. @@yyellow@@N paint on the name cartouches has faded to a warm cream against the @@bsandstone@@N, and @@cblue@@N faience border tiles run below each recess in a continuous course that is remarkably well-preserved. The smell of mummification chemistry is strongest here of any room in the vault.
~
