@@yThe Embalmer's Gallery@@N~
Illustrated burial rites cover both walls of this gallery in a procedural sequence depicting the specific embalming methods used for the secondary pharaoh-lords interred on this floor. The illustrations are detailed to the point of technical instruction: the chemical concentrations, the tool types, the specific prayers at each stage, and the quality of linen for each wrapping phase. @@yGold-highlighted@@N key steps mark the most critical interventions in the process, and the @@cblue@@N borders separate the illustrations from the accompanying text in a clean visual hierarchy.
~
