#10271
@@yThe Soul Weighing Chamber@@N~
A giant carved scale dominates the center of this chamber, its arms still in balance after millennia, its carved pans holding carved hearts on one side and a carved feather on the other. The scale is the divine judgment mechanism of the pyramid's faith, shown here at the moment of perfect equilibrium that represents successful judgment. @@cLapis lazuli@@N inlay covers the feather in dense blue that makes it visually dominant despite its notional weightlessness, and @@yyellow gold@@N fills the carved hearts with a warmth that seems deliberate — the emphasis of value over righteousness. The chamber smells of the same dry, ancient chemistry as the rest of the vault.
~
