#10273
@@yThe Mummy Lords' Wing@@N~
The primary hall of the secondary pharaoh-lords' section of the Eternal Vault, its walls carrying the full hieratic portraits of the mummy lords interred in the vault recesses throughout this floor. Each portrait shows its subject in full ceremonial regalia: crown, crook, flail, and the specific divine attributes of their individual authority. The quality of carving varies; the lords depicted earlier in the hall have finer portraits than those toward the north, suggesting the workmanship was declining as the vault neared capacity. @@RBlood-red@@N threat indicators now appear regularly in the border decorations.
~
