#10274
@@yA Burial Alcove@@N~
A deep alcove containing a single sealed sarcophagus of slightly larger dimensions than those in the Hall of Eternal Rest — a minor lord rather than a major one, given its placement here rather than in the main hall, but clearly of sufficient standing to merit individualized burial rather than communal interment. The sarcophagus's cartouche names have been deliberately erased, the name removed by someone at some point in the pyramid's active life. The reasons for the erasure are not recorded.
~
